  "system": {
    "description": "<p>A rope dagger is a flexible weapon similar to a whip chain, featuring a 20&rsquo; length of flexible rope or cord, with a sharp, short dagger on the end of it. Rope daggers also contain a ribbon or features, to aid in fighting with the weapon. A character can strike opponents up to 20&rsquo; away with a rope dagger. Because a rope dagger can wrap around an enemy&rsquo;s leg or other limb, rope daggers can be used to perform trip attacks, and do not provoke AoO when doing so. If the character is tripped during their own trip attempt, the character can drop the whip to avoid being tripped. Rope daggers are considered to be bullwhips for the purpose of feats and equipment.</p>",
